HEADWORD: Grucche
<hw>Grucche</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Grudge</er>.]</ety> <def>To murmur; to grumble.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What aileth you, thus for <qex>grucche</qex> and groan.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grudge</ent>⟦br⟧
